TRADITIONAL C IS DIFFERENT

On many UNIX systems, to compile this program,
you must give the command

   cc main.c -lm

The -lm option tells the loader to attach the
mathematics library.  In ANSI C systems, the
programmer really should not have to use this
option.  However, the use of the -lm option
predates the days of ANSI C, and many UNIX
systems still do things the old way.

---
Note that in our program we wrote

   int main()

instead of

   int main(void)

In traditional C, there is no keyword void.
